“I need some of this sweet cock.” He murmurs, yanking open Peter’s zipper and pulling his soft cock through the slit in his underwear.

Peter chuckles vacantly as his head falls back onto the couch. He feels muted heat surround his cock, and not much else. “Okay.”

by ChickenNoodleSoop

“Tony, something’s approaching.” It was now that he noticed the blaring lights, the screen revealing a small blue dot getting closer and closer to the ship. What was it? Was it another one of Thanos’ henchmen? Tony was too weak to fight any of them, and the days without food was weakening Nebula. They had to hide…
“Good to know we’re on the same page.” Wait… he said that out loud? Whoops.
His breath was labored as they ran to the ship’s boiler room, which was a chore because the ship was a damn circle and climbing was hard. Especially after having a damned panic attack. Nebula had to carry him half of the way, and shit was she strong. He got it, her arms and legs were half tin can, but, that’s still tough regardless. They reached the boiler room, Nebula locking the door behind them and hiding behind the heating system. The technology was amazing, but, right now was not the time to geek out.

body:
Marvel Movie review #3: Iron Man 2

My third review in my Marvel Marathon on the road to ENDGAME. My review of The incredible hulk.   and my review of the first iron man

Rating 4.5 out of 5 

What I liked: 

  • BABY PETER!!!!!!!!
  • Rhodey is like an angry big brother
  • Natasha Natalie
  • PEPPERONY
  • BABY PETER
  • Nick Fury is a tired dad 
  • “I got my eye on you”
  • Phil Coulson 
  • Tony throwing away strawberries and not getting a single one in the can.
  • Tony Stark created a new element. HE DID THAT!
  • “DROP YOUR SOCKS AND GRAB YOUR CROCS”
  • BABY PETER

What I disliked:

  1. Hammer is really annoying and somewhat unnecessary
  2. I feel like Ivan was taken down a little too fast. 

My favorite scenes: This movie has sooooo many iconic moments, so I will try and narrow it down.

  • The boxing ring scene
  • The car race scene is incredible and the “ARE YOU OUT OF YOUR MIND?!” “I WAS ATTACKED!” iconic
  • Tony sitting in the donut
  • The scene where Howard left the message for Tony absolutely kills me every time. “my greatest creation is you”

My Background/Memories with this movie: 

I watched this with my best friend for the first time at the lake

Things I noticed this viewing:

  • I feel really stupid but I just now noticed the Senator is the hydra agent from the winter soldier. 
  • “Its you, its always been you” That hurts a lot more now.
  • They play “Another one bites the dust” during the show down between Rhodey and Tony… More foreshadowing????
  • That Captain America reference

Random thoughts:

  1. Howard reminds me a little bit of Walt Disney
